Analysis of Main Target Image  
• Block Count & Layers:  
  – There are a total of six blocks.  
    • Four vertical orange cylinders on the bottom “layer.”  
    • Two flat green rectangular blocks on the top “layer.”  
  – Hence, the structure is built in two layers: the bottom layer of four vertical cylinders, and a top layer of two green rectangular blocks side‐by‐side.  

• Spatial Arrangement:  
  – Bottom Layer: The four orange cylinders stand upright in a roughly square formation.  
  – Top Layer: Two green rectangular prisms lie flat across the tops of the four cylinders, each spanning front‐to‐back and placed next to each other (so the longer edges run left‐to‐right in the final view).  

Selecting Blocks from the Dictionary  
1. Four upright orange cylinders match dictionary block #7 (the vertical cylinder).  
2. Two flat green rectangular blocks with their length oriented left‐to‐right match dictionary block #1.  

List of Needed Block Indices  
• Orange cylinders: #7 × 4  
• Green rectangular blocks: #1 × 2  

Assembly Instructions  
{  
  Step1: Move block with index 7  
  Step2: Move block with index 7  
  Step3: Move block with index 7  
  Step4: Move block with index 7  
  Step5: Move block with index 1  
  Step6: Move block with index 1  
}
